id: AIC-NAV-001
type: module
owner: business
extends: project.intent

module: aic navigate
command: aic navigate --query "your task description"
description: >
  Traverses the project intent structure based on a natural language
  query and assembles a scoped context package containing exactly
  the right intent files for that task.
  No AI involved. No code generated. Pure deterministic traversal.
  Output is ready to paste into any AI tool.

behaviors:
  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B1
    intent: |
      Parse the query to extract component name, language, and action.
      Match component name against known /business subfolders.
      Match language against known language folders in project root.
      Match action from keywords: fix, create, migrate, explain, audit.
      If component is ambiguous list all business folder names
      and ask developer to clarify. Do not guess.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B2
    intent: |
      Always read project.intent first regardless of query.
      It is always in scope for every task without exception.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B3
    intent: |
      If component matched read business/<Component>/module.intent.
      If language matched read <language>/language.intent.
      If both matched read <language>/<Component>/<Component>.intent.
      Never read sibling component folders — scope pollution prevention.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B4
    intent: |
      Assemble all read files into one structured context block.
      Each section separated by a border line with its title.
      Add header identifying what the context covers.
      Add footer instructing developer to paste into AI before their question.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B5
    intent: |
      Support three output modes:
        Default  — print to terminal
        --copy   — copy to clipboard via pyperclip
        --file   — write to .aic/context/<query-slug>.txt
      Gracefully fall back to terminal if clipboard copy fails.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B6
    intent: |
      If no component or language matched in query:
        List all available business folder names.
        Print helpful message suggesting query refinement.
        Exit cleanly — not an error.

  - id: AIC-NAV-001-B7
    intent: |
      Print a summary line before the context block:
        "Context assembled for: component=X, language=Y"
        "Files included: N"
      Helps developer confirm the right files were picked.

journeys:
  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "fix UserService in python"
    outcome: |
      project.intent, module.intent, python.intent,
      and UserService.intent assembled into one context block.
      Printed to terminal ready to paste into AI.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "fix UserService" with --copy
    outcome: |
      Same context assembled and copied to clipboard automatically.
      Developer pastes directly into AI chat.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "something unrelated"
    outcome: |
      No match found.
      All available business module names listed.
      Helpful refinement suggestion printed.
      Exit 0 — not an error.

  - actor: Developer
    trigger: Runs aic navigate --query "payment flow" with --file
    outcome: |
      Context written to .aic/context/payment-flow.txt
      File path printed to terminal.

  - actor: Autonomous AI agent (future v2)
    trigger: Reads NAVIGATION.intent from project root directly
    outcome: |
      Follows step by step navigation instructions.
      Self-navigates without running aic navigate command.
      Used when AIC is not installed in the environment.

failure-modes:
  - scenario: AIC not initialised
    response: Exit code 1 — suggest aic init

  - scenario: No component or language matched
    response: Exit code 0 — list available components, suggest refinement

  - scenario: Clipboard copy fails
    response: Fall back to terminal output, print warning

  - scenario: File write fails
    response: Fall back to terminal output, print warning

implementation-note: |
  This command contains zero LLM calls.
  All phases are fully deterministic.
  Phase 1: query parsing
  Phase 2: file traversal
  Phase 3: context assembly
  Phase 4: output

  v1 manual note:
  Developer runs aic navigate, copies output, pastes into AI chat.
  MCP server wrapping this command is planned for v2.